Collections - ArrayList : kCopies

Write a method named kCopies that accepts an ArrayList of integers as a parameter and replaces every integer of value k with k copies of itself. 
For example, if the list stores [4, 1, 2, 0, 3] before the method is called, it should store [4, 4, 4, 4, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3] after the method finishes executing.
Zeroes and negative numbers should be removed from the list.

 public static void kCopies(ArrayList<Integer> listOfInts) {
        ArrayList<Integer> modifiedList = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int targetNumber : listOfInts) {
            if (targetNumber > 0) {
                for (int j = 0; j < targetNumber; j++) {
                    modifiedList.add(targetNumber);
                }
            }
        }
        listOfInts.clear();
        listOfInts.addAll(modifiedList);
    }



